NOTE: why this strange file organization ?

in boost prior 1_34_0, the impl for "utf8_codecvt_facet.cpp" used to live in:
    libs/serialization/src/utf8_codecvt_facet.cpp

since boost 1_34_0, the impl for "utf8_codecvt_facet.cpp" moved to:
    libs/detail/utf8_codecvt_facet.cpp
    where the original path now holds a shell that includes both the hpp and the cpp.

references:
    http://www.edobashira.com/2010/03/using-boost-code-facet-for-reading-utf8.html
    http://semmel.wordpress.com/2011/01/19/processing-utf-8-text-in-c/

    http://boost.org/doc/libs/1_46_1/boost/detail/utf8_codecvt_facet.hpp
    http://boost.org/doc/libs/1_46_1/libs/detail/utf8_codecvt_facet.cpp
    http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_46_1/libs/serialization/src/utf8_codecvt_facet.cpp

    http://boost.org/doc/libs/1_34_0/boost/detail/utf8_codecvt_facet.hpp
    http://boost.org/doc/libs/1_34_0/libs/detail/utf8_codecvt_facet.cpp
    http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_34_0/libs/serialization/src/utf8_codecvt_facet.cpp

    http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_32_0/libs/serialization/src/utf8_codecvt_facet.cpp
